OL,3,CWhy Guernsey's parental leave is among
OL,4,Cthe worst in the Western world
OL,6,FOne mother, Constance Walden, says:
OL,7,F"Every mother I spoke to at some stage
OL,8,Fwas concerned that, financially, they
OL,9,Fweren't being paid for a period of
OL,10,Ftheir maternity at least. It's a shame
OL,11,Fwe don't have that same assistance."
OL,13,FConstance adds that some islanders are
OL,14,Fhaving to dip into savings to cover
OL,15,Fthe difference.
OL,17,FShe explains: "Obviously, it wasn't a
OL,18,Fsurprise knowing what I was going to
OL,19,Fbe paid; it was part of my contract.
